control, with the National Rifle Association? We are here to ask Al
D'Amato why he continually does that.''
</P>
<P>
   A spokesman for D'Amato, who was making a campaign swing through
upstate cities Sunday, countered that D'Amato was in fact tougher
on crime than his Democratic opponent. ``Chuck Schumer is trying to
