<HEADLINE>
BC SUSPENDS LEE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL VEGA  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOSTON _ Junior running back Quinton Lee was suspended
indefinitely from Boston College's football team after he was
arrested by Boston police early Sunday morning at an off-campus
party and charged with assault and battery on an officer and
disorderly conduct.
</P>
<P>
   According to police reports, Lee, 22, of Houston, was spotted by
officers holding a plastic cup of beer at 12:30 a.m. at a party at
10 Sutherland Road near Cleveland Circle. Lee was approached by a
Boston police officer and told to empty the contents of the cup
into a sewer drain. But, according to police sources, Lee refused
and instead finished his drink and defiantly threw the cup on the
ground.
</P>
<P>
   Lee reportedly argued with the police officer, resisted arrest,
and was jailed overnight at District 14 before he was released
Sunday. He will be arraigned in Brighton District Court Monday.
</P>
<P>
   BC coach Tom O'Brien said Sunday Lee was suspended indefinitely
for violation of team rules and offered no further comment.
</P>
<P>
   According to BC spokesman Reid Oslin, Lee could be subject to
further disciplinary action by Bob Sherwood, BC's dean of student
development. However, Oslin declined to speculate on what action
could be taken, citing Lee's pending arraignment.
</P>
</TEXT>
