<SLUG> BC-OBIT-LAIRD-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
W. FREDERICK LAIRD, COLUMBIA GAS SYSTEM EXECUTIVE, 79 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN: Del.)  (js) 
 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   W. Frederick Laird, former chairman and chief executive officer
of the Columbia Gas System, died of cancer Tuesday at Christiana
Hospital in Newark, Del. Laird, who lived in Greenville, Del., was
79.
</P>
<P>
   Born in London, Ohio, Laird was hired by Columbia in 1951. By
the 1970s, Columbia was one of the largest gas companies in the
nation, serving 10 percent of all customers.
</P>
<P>
   Laird, who served as chairman and chief executive from 1980
until his mandatory retirement at age 65 in 1984, is survived by
his wife of 55 years, Jane; two sons, Frederick, of Plainfield,
N.J., and John, of New York, and four grandchildren.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
