<HEADLINE>
D-BACKS AT BAT: KINGS OF THE K  
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By BOB COHN  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX - The Diamondbacks probably won't lose 100 games this
year, but they did nail one dubious achievement against the Atlanta
Braves on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   No National League team in history has struck out as often.
</P>
<P>
   When  &UR; Yamil Benitez fanned against &UR; Bruce Chen in the fifth
inning of a 10-0 loss to the Braves, it was strikeout No. 1,204,
breaking the previous record held by the 1968 New York Mets (who,
by the way, won the World Series the next season).
</P>
<P>
   ``He (Chen) threw the ball right there, and everybody was
swinging like crazy,'' Benitez said. ``Especially myself.''
</P>
<P>
   Braves pitchers struck out seven Diamondbacks, bringing the
season total to 1,207. With five games remaining, the major league
record of 1,268 held by the 1996 Detroit Tigers is presumably out
of reach.
</P>
<P>
   One of the strikeout victims was  &UR; Devon White, whose whiff in
the ninth inning made it an even 100 for the season. The
Diamondbacks now have four players with 100 strikeouts or more:
White, rookie  &UR; David
 &UR; Dellucci (102), rookie  &UR; Travis Lee (123) and &UR; Jay Bell (124).  &UR; Matt
 &UR; Williams and  &UR; Andy Fox are within range with 98 and 94,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
   Manager  &UR; Buck Showalter, who was aware of the mark, cites a
couple of reasons.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a problem for most clubs that struggle,'' he said.
``Pitch selection. Hitting behind in the count a lot. Pitch
recognition. A lot of young players. Also, strikeouts are up
because of the long ball. People will give up strikeouts for home
runs. It's more and more of a tendency.''
</P>
<P>
   Squib hits &QL; 
A throwing error by catcher  &UR; Damian Miller ended the Diamondbacks'
streak of 79 straight errorless innings, a club record. The
Diamondbacks have committed 97 errors this season, tied for second
fewest in the National League with San Francisco and New York. The
Braves lead with 90.
</P>
<P>
   Following a difficult pregnancy, &UR; Josneil Daal, the wife of
Diamondbacks left-hander  &UR; Omar Daal, gave birth early Saturday
morning. Josneil and baby  &UR; Nicolas, born a month premature and the
couple's second son, are doing fine.
</P>
<P>
   Williams has been named Diamondbacks winner of the
 &UR; Roberto Clemente Man of the Year Award. Williams is eligible to win
the national Clemente award. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
