<P>
   KELSO-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ It's fitting that school
officials in this small town 30 miles east of Austin have decided
to let the high school students wear some shirts untucked to
school. By going to school with untucked shirts, the students are
conforming to the community standard, right? (Kelso, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED.
