<P>
   Editors, attention managing editors, wire editors:
</P>
<P>
   Because of its volume, The New York Times News Service will not
move full texts of the Clinton grand jury testimony, the Lewinsky
testimony and the rest of the Starr documents that were made public
by the House Judiciary Committee this morning.
</P>
<P>
   Once they are in electronic form, The Associated Press will
provide the full texts in ASCII and HTML formats at an ftp site and
as Adobe PDF files through AP Send. However, the ftp site is not
the same site the AP used to deliver the earlier OIC report. See
their advisories for additional information.
</P>
<P>
   The AP has also decided not to release the full text over normal
news wires.
</P>
<P>
   Later in the day we will send a complete CLINTON-ADVISORY,
advising you of coverage plans for Tuesday's editions of The New
York Times.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The New York Times News Service &LR;
