<HEADLINE>
`LADY' IS CLASSIC DISNEY; `CITY OF ANGELS' DOESN'T FLY 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES:  &UR; ``Lady and the Tramp'' &LR;  _ The Hepburn-Tracy of
the animated canine world return in one of Disney's finest films.
The perfect fit of form and function (a cartoon romance) also
features Peggy Lee as the voice of a sultry canine. Who can resist
the most famous eating scene this side of ``Tom Jones''? One of the
few films that deserves to be called a masterpiece.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``City of Angels'' &LR;  _ The remake of Wim Wenders's edgy fantasy,
``Wings of Desire,'' doesn't fly. It's bigger and splashier than
its source material, and stars Nicolas Cage and Meg Ryan, but it
remains earthbound. Cage's angelic observations fall flat.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``Suicide Kings''  &LR; _ Christopher Walken as a crime boss
kidnapped by preppies spends most of the mystery thriller bound to
a chair. And he gives one of his great performances with both hands
tied. Henry Thomas, whose post-``E.T.'' career is taking off, is
terrific as one of the preppy kidnappers, and Denis Leary, as
another hitman, gives an over-the-top _ in face, Walkenesque _
performance.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``The Last Don II''  &LR; _ One was enough. Besides, isn't the title
an oxy-moron?
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
---- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ALL THAT JAZZ: Jazz fans are in luck because Rhapsody Films of
Lyme, Conn., is having a sale. ``Last of the Blue Devils,'' ``The
Gospel According to Al Green,'' ``Mingus,'' ``Sonny Rollins: Live
at Loren,'' and dozens of other titles are all being offered for
$14.95 or less. Call (860) 434-3610.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Sept. 22:  &LR; ``Addams Family Reunion,'' ``Happy Together,''
``Nightwatch,'' ``Fallen Angels.''  &UR; Sept. 29:  &LR; ``The Object of My
Affection,'' ``The Song of Songs,'' ``The Trial,'' ``The Jungle
Book: Mowgli's Story,'' ``Milo,'' ``A Foreign Affair,'' ``Two Girls
and a Guy,'' ``The Devil Is a Woman,'' ``Chinese Box,'' ``The Flame
of New Orleans,'' ``Paulie.''  &UR; Oct. 6 &LR; : ``Lost in Space,''
``Holiday Toons,'' ``Fairy Tale: A True Story.''  &UR; Oct. 13: &LR;  ``L.A.
Confidential,'' ``The Big One,'' ``Black Dog,'' ``It's a Gift,''
``Million Dollar Legs,'' ``You Can't Cheat an Honest Man,''
``You're Telling Me,'' ``The Lost World,'' ``I Got the Hook Up.''
 &UR; Oct. 20 &LR; : ``Species 2,'' ``Chitty Chitty Bang Bang,'' ``Red
Corner,'' ``Hope Floats.''  &UR; Oct. 27:  &LR; ``The Lion King II: Simba's
Pride,'' ``Operation Delta Force 2.''  &UR; Nov. 6 &LR; : ``Godzilla.''
</P>
