<P>
   CLINTON-VIDEOTAPE (Washington) _ President Clinton's videotaped
testimony to the grand jury provided ammunition to both sides of
the debate over whether he should be impeached. Clinton stubbornly
jousted with his interrogators, quibbling over definitions of
``sexual relations,'' attacking independent counsel Kenneth Starr's
motives and evading some questions with claims of lapsed memory. He
also exuded empathy for subordinates including Monica Lewinsky and
secretary Betty Currie, and appealed that his personal privacy be
respected. By STEWART M. POWELL.
