Colman will become executive vice president-human resources. Colman
had been vice president-human resources for GE's electric engines
business in Cincinnati. (Thurston, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   SOUTHERN-TEXAS _ Southern Co. is purchasing a small power plant
in Texas, its first move into that state. Purchase price not
disclosed, but Texas is one of several regions the company has
targeted for power sector investments. (Quinn, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   FOREX _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Update on Austin Forex International,
the foreign currency company being investigated by Texas state
authorities. (Tyson, Austin American-Statesman) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   TREE-VILLAGE _ Lost Tree Village, like plenty of other gated
communities in South Florida, offers its residents a country club,
beach house, pro shops, even a chapel. But what sets it apart is
its optional, residential tax write-off _ an elite, IRS-approved
philanthropy, which allows donors to take a charitable tax
deduction for up to 50 percent of their adjusted gross income in a
single year. (Murawski, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TECH-TOOLS _ I wouldn't expect much from a machine that claims
to copy and scan, with an automatic document feeder and optical
character recognition, all for a list price of $250. In the case of
the Lumina PCC, I was mistaken. (Warner, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TECH-MEDIA _ If there's one thing that's certain about PCs, it's
that sooner or later they break down. The October issue of PC World
devotes its cover story to how to figure out what's wrong and fix
it. Better yet, the issue offers tips on how to improve the
performance of PCs that are working. (Haddad, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TECH-REPORT _ For most of this century, bigger was better and
biggest was best, whether the topic was a new ocean liner or a
record zucchini. But that course has been reversed in the digital
age. Small now stands tall. (Ghirardini, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TECH-KIDS _ Small Wonders'' was a huge hit in the Farris
household, in Mableton. The PC fighting game of action toys
captivated reviewer Jesse Farris, 12, and his brothers _ Jacob, 9,
and Joseph, 8 _ with its vivid graphics and fierce fighting action.
``We play it a lot,'' Jesse said. ``It's a lot of fun.'' (Davis,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TECHNOBUDDY _ By now, many of you have a whole new set of
problems. You have installed Windows 98. Don't get me wrong. This
isn't going to be a diatribe (well, I will rant just a little)
against Windows 98. But if you're like me, you spent several years
tuning up Windows 95. Things like that take a lot of time and a lot
of tweaking. (Husted, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   MAC-REPORT _ Despite Microsoft Word's hegemony, Mac users have
plenty of good choices when it comes to writing programs. All are
less expensive than Word, which now costs a whopping $369.95, and
offer most of its features. (Haddad, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   CYBERSCENE _ Today let's visit a store where shoplifting is
encouraged. Actually, there are literally thousands of stores like
this. They're all located on the Internet and each contains more
software than you could ever use. You're welcome to drop by and
download as much as your hard disk can hold. (Husted, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
