dollars and upheld two world heavyweight titles in the last two
years, his marriage and family life has been in disarray. Soon
after he and wife Janice were wed, he says he realized it was a
mistake and discussed an annulment with her. Later, he fathered two
children out of wedlock. (With Janice giving birth nine days ago,
he has had three children within a year). He and Janice have gone
through marriage counseling, and he says their future is cloudy. He
realizes his image as a Christian will take a hit with the
revelations, but says he is a human being who makes mistakes and is
learning from them. (Schultz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) WITH
