   &UR; By BILL TAMMEUS &LR;  &QC;   &UR; Bill Tammeus, The Kansas City Star
 &LR;  Release of Mr. Clinton's videotaped testimony raises the question
of whether there's a market for pay-perjure-view TV.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; QUOTABLES FROM NBC'S 'THE TONIGHT SHOW WITH JAY LENO' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``How many have read the Ken Starr report? It said in the report
that Monica Lewinsky once brought President Clinton a pizza, and
then gave him oral sex. You know, I used to think it was great just
getting extra cheese!''
</P>
<P>
   ``This has gotta be a strange time to own a newsstand. 'Hey kid!
Quit looking at that Time magazine! Put that Newsweek down! Filthy
kids, looking at that Wall Street Journal.'''
</P>
<P>
   ``It's probably the first time in history men aren't grabbing
the sports section first. 'Honey, will you give me the oral
section? I wanna see how Clinton did over the weekend.'''
</P>
<P>
   ``It's good to see America reading again, isn't it? If Bill
Clinton is remembered for anything, he helped make the country more
literate. Everybody's reading.''
</P>
<P>
   ``It is really unbelievable. You can't even joke. But I did
learn some stuff from reading it. Did you know this? Anybody know
what the ``D.C.'' stands for in Washington D.C.? 'Disappearing
Cigars.'''
</P>
<P>
   ``That House Judiciary committee met to decide whether to
release President Clinton's videotape testimony before the Grand
Jury to the public. Today, the Democrats said yes, they will go
along with the tape being released, as long as the hair gel scene
is edited out so they can get a PG rating.''
</P>
<P>
   ``A lot of people are comparing what's happening with Clinton to
what happened with Nixon. Think it's the same thing? I don't think
there's any comparison. I doubt there's any 22-year-old in the
world who would have sex with Nixon and then be willing to talk
about it.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Do you know the Miss America contestants can now use fanny
glue? They use it to keep their bathing suits in place. They
actually glue the back of the bathing suits to their rear ends to
keep the suits up. What a great gift this would make for your
plumber or repairman.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Know what I love about the Emmys? You ever notice when the
winner's coming down the aisle towards the podium, the announcer
always gives you those statistics. 'This is his second Emmy in
eight nominations' or 'This is her third try after having never won
before.' You know, give the statistics people want. 'She's on her
fourth boob job.' 'Although he's a romantic lead, he's really
gay.'''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; QUOTABLES FROM NBC'S 'LATE NIGHT WITH CONAN O'BRIEN' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``Yesterday at a luncheon, the Democratic National Chairman
introduced President Clinton and praised him for his 'moral
leadership.' Then the two of them high-fived and spent the rest of
the day at Hooters.''
</P>
<P>
   ``It's been reported that President Clinton is going to meet
with a minister once a week to help him avoid temptation. The only
problem is she's a really hot minister.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Yesterday in New York, President Clinton attended the Broadway
musical 'The Lion King.' To make sure the President wasn't
embarrassed by the play, the producers removed the scene with
Simba, Nala and the cigar.''
</P>
<P>
   ``The House Judiciary Committee is considering releasing the
videotaped testimony where President Clinton talks about his
relationship with Monica Lewinsky. Apparently the tape is called
'Too Hot for Jerry Springer.'''
</P>
<P>
   ``Yesterday, Monica Lewinsky's rabbi lashed out at President
Clinton for shaming the country and called him a boy in a man's
job. The rabbi also said he's encouraging Lewinsky to find a nice
Jewish president.''
</P>
<P>
   ``A public relations expert says if Monica Lewinsky wants to put
her life back together, she should get married. Monica says she
hasn't received any wedding proposals yet, but she has been invited
to several bachelor parties.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Yesterday Czech President Vaclav Havel and President Clinton
had a joint press conference and nine out of 10 questions were
about the sex scandal. Today, Havel and Clinton announced they are
going to be the new hosts of MTV's 'LoveLine.'''
</P>
<P>
   ``Yesterday, Newt Gingrich told a group of Republicans that
President Clinton is a woman-hater. In response, the President
said, 'Apparently. he has not been paying attention.'''
</P>
<P>
   ``They are talking about releasing the videotape of President
Clinton's Grand Jury testimony that shows that he got very agitated
during the four hours of questioning. Mostly because that's the
longest he's ever gone without oral sex.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Republicans say they decided not to release 120 sections of
Kenneth Starr's report because they were too sexually explicit.
Plus they're saving those parts for a pay-per-view special.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Kenneth Starr's daughter will be a freshman at Stanford
University this fall where Chelsea Clinton is already a sophomore.
Chelsea says it's great to be back at school and she can hardly
wait for freshman hazing to begin.''
</P>
<P>
   ``The other day somebody slipped a lit firecracker through the
mail slot of Monica Lewinsky's home in California. Monica said she
was shaken up, but not half as much as the time someone played a
trick on her with an exploding cigar.''
</P>
