   &UR; CITY STREETS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   On a recent visit to Manhattan from New Jersey, I took my
9-year-old son, Brendan, on the subway. I noticed he looked a bit
nervous walking through the station at Port Authority, as his
subway experience was very limited. As the doors shut on the car, I
could see the uneasiness on his face.
</P>
<P>
   The train started moving, and as we came to a bend in the
tracks, the conductor loudly announced something that was
unintelligible because of the defective speaker system. I noticed
