<P>
   Let's Get Our Priorities Straight Department:
</P>
<P>
   It was halftime at a Knicks game at the Garden earlier this year
and Barry Baum was standing in line at the ATM, in front of four
boys, each around 11 years old.
</P>
<P>
   ``I want to buy the Knicks shorts,'' said the one boy with an
ATM card. ``But my mother said I can only use the ATM machine for
emergencies.''
</P>
<P>
   His friends had no doubts. They nodded their heads in agreement
as one spoke out. ``But this is an emergency,'' he advised.
</P>
<P>
   Baum finished his transaction, walked a few steps away and
turned back to see the decision. The card carrier was eagerly
typing the code into the machine.
</P>
<P>
   Saul Bellow and his wife were guests at a dinner party held by
our neighbors, Dorothy and Phil Zaro, at their vacation home in
Vermont.
</P>
<P>
   Some days later, back in Westchester County, Dorothy Zaro was
having her hair done. ``I had Saul Bellow for dinner this past
weekend,'' she said. There was silence for a moment. Then the
hairdresser replied: ``Do you know, I have never had that dish. Was
it good?''
</P>
<P>
   _ BOB GROSSBAUM
</P>
<P>
   The group at the Brooklyn Museum of Art was beginning its tour
of American paintings and Lillian Kanfer, a guide at the museum,
was about to start her lecture. Suddenly a woman in the group
rushed to the front and pointed to a figure in the foreground.
</P>
<P>
   ``Don't touch,'' another member of the group warned her.
</P>
<P>
   ``Why not?'' asked the woman. ``It's not wet.''
</P>
<P>
   Michael Stinchcomb, a weekend gardener in the Hamptons, was
grateful to a friend who told him that she used inverted wine
bottles full of water to keep her potted plants from drying out
during the week.
</P>
<P>
   One weekend he lent his house to a horticulturally challenged
Manhattanite, left some inverted wine bottles and told his friend
to be sure to water the flowers when he arrived. When Stinchcomb
picked up his telephone messages, he was amused to hear: ``I don't
know what to do. Which plants drink chardonnay, which drink merlot
and which drink champagne?''
