<P>
   &UR; QUOTABLES FROM NBC'S 'THE TONIGHT SHOW WITH JAY LENO' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``How many have read the Ken Starr report? It said in the report
that Monica Lewinsky once brought President Clinton a pizza, and
then gave him oral sex. You know, I used to think it was great just
getting extra cheese!''
</P>
<P>
   ``This has gotta be a strange time to own a newsstand. 'Hey kid!
Quit looking at that Time magazine! Put that Newsweek down! Filthy
kids, looking at that Wall Street Journal.'''
</P>
<P>
   ``It's probably the first time in history men aren't grabbing
the sports section first. 'Honey, will you give me the oral
section? I wanna see how Clinton did over the weekend.'''
</P>
<P>
   ``It's good to see America reading again, isn't it? If Bill
Clinton is remembered for anything, he helped make the country more
literate. Everybody's reading.''
</P>
<P>
   ``It is really unbelievable. You can't even joke. But I did
learn some stuff from reading it. Did you know this? Anybody know
what the ``D.C.'' stands for in Washington D.C.? 'Disappearing
Cigars.'''
</P>
<P>
   ``That House Judiciary committee met to decide whether to
release President Clinton's videotape testimony before the Grand
Jury to the public. Today, the Democrats said yes, they will go
along with the tape being released, as long as the hair gel scene
is edited out so they can get a PG rating.''
</P>
<P>
   ``A lot of people are comparing what's happening with Clinton to
what happened with Nixon. Think it's the same thing? I don't think
there's any comparison. I doubt there's any 22-year-old in the
world who would have sex with Nixon and then be willing to talk
about it.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Do you know the Miss America contestants can now use fanny
glue? They use it to keep their bathing suits in place. They
actually glue the back of the bathing suits to their rear ends to
keep the suits up. What a great gift this would make for your
plumber or repairman.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Know what I love about the Emmys? You ever notice when the
winner's coming down the aisle towards the podium, the announcer
always gives you those statistics. 'This is his second Emmy in
eight nominations' or 'This is her third try after having never won
before.' You know, give the statistics people want. 'She's on her
fourth boob job.' 'Although he's a romantic lead, he's really
gay.'''
</P>
