 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    `Complete' offers 225 tracks by Hank Sr.
 &HT;    By Russ Devault
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Except for seldom-recorded bluesman Robert Johnson, few artists
have had their entire recording careers gathered into one box. But
``The Complete Hank Williams'' just about does it for the seminal
country artist.
</P>
<P>
   The 10-CD set contains 225 tracks, including 53 previously
unreleased. Prices vary, with retailers who have it charging $140
to $170, so call around. Grade: A.
</P>
<P>
   -- Sheryl Crow, ``The Globe Sessions'' (A&AMP;M). In stores next
Tuesday. Grade: B.
</P>
<P>
   -- George Clinton &AMP; the P-Funk All Stars, ``Dope Dogs'' (Dogone
Records). The Godfather of Funk is back _ again.
</P>
<P>
   -- Ice Cube, ``War'' (Priority). That's first half of two-CD set
``War &AMP; Peace.'' Due Nov. 17, with ``Peace'' coming next year.
</P>
<P>
   -- Chris Isaak, ``Speak of the Devil'' (Reprise). Grade: A-.
</P>
<P>
   -- Sparks, ``Plagiarism'' (Oglio Records). Faith No More, other
acts help brothers duo Ron and Russell Mael update their music.
</P>
<P>
   -- Vanilla Ice, ``Hard to Swallow'' (Republic/Universal). Could
he happen again? Album due Oct. 20.
</P>
