<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    The Television new season:Tuesday
 &HT;    By Bob Longino, Lyle V. Harris, Phil Kloer, and Drew Jubera
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   -- ``The Hughleys'' 8:30 p.m. EDT, ABC _ It's this season's
second _ and better _ sitcom about an African-American family
moving to an all-white 'burb. Grade: B
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Encore! Encore!'' 8:30 p.m. EDT, NBC _ Nathan Lane's an
opera singer. Then the curtain really falls. Grade: D
</P>
<P>
   -- ``JAG'' 8 p.m. EDT, CBS _ Last season's cliffhanger continues
with planes flying and a gung-ho fight for survival behind enemy
lines.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Spin City'' 9 p.m. EDT, ABC _ It starts later this season _
which means even more jokes about sex.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Just Shoot Me'' 9 p.m. EDT, NBC _ Who needs ``Frasier'' on
Tuesdays anymore? David Spade and the Blush gang prove they're
rising stars.
</P>
<P>
   Grade: A-
</P>
<P>
   Some tired old shows deserve to die:
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Mad About You'' 8 p.m. EDT, NBC _ Is there an award Helen
Hunt hasn't won? There's little wondering why she's hanging around
here _ where the humor has her stuck near naked out on the streets
of New York. It's called $1 million an episode. Grade: C
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Home Improvement'' 8 p.m. EDT, ABC _ The eighth season
begins. Tim goes white water rafting. Ha ha. Isn't it time to hang
up the tools?
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Working'' 9:30 p.m. EDT, NBC _ It's never worked.
</P>
