<HEADLINE>
WINTER (AND FALL) WHITE  
(JT)
</HEADLINE>
   By ANNE-MARIE SCHIRO   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Did you grow up hearing you should never wear white
after Labor Day? Well, forget it. Chanel and Prada featured white
shoes, boots and bags for fall, reminding the fashion world of the
white go-go boots Courreges showed with his space age clothes in
the 1960s. And with the millennium approaching, white looks
ultramodern again.
</P>
<P>
   Chanel's white ankle boots ($765), Prada's white wedgies ($360)
and Miu Miu's white Mary Janes ($250) can all be found at Neiman
Marcus, along with Manolo Blahnik's high-heeled mules with
Swiss-cheese holes ($455).
</P>
<P>
   Barneys New York has sporty white leather gloves in its private
label collection ($110 to $185), Prada's knee-high boots ($670),
Michel Perry's ankle boots ($455), Jil Sander's loafers ($425), two
Prada handbags with short shoulder straps ($680 and $740), Drea
Kadilak's felt cloche hat ($195), and white-framed sunglasses by
Calvin Klein ($195), Isaac Mizrahi ($165) and Jean LaFont ($210).
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
