   EXP-CLINTON-IMAGE (Washington) _ how the president came across:
Bill Clinton has always loved nothing better than a tough audience,
and in the end, that is how he treated Kenneth W. Starr's grand
jury, starting shakily, then warming to his task, unspooling every
tool of wounded dignity, controlled anger and confidant elaboration
at his command in a performance filled with his trademark touches.
By Todd S. Purdum.
