as just more embarrassment heaped on the man, his office, and the
nation he leads.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's not worth what we're paying for this fiasco,'' said
Oubre, a history and economics major.
</P>
<P>
   The six students, a mix of Democrats and Republicans and one
Independent _ Oubre _ passed around a box of Kix breakfast cereal
and alternately hissed, laughed or rolled their at the eyes at
Clinton's definitions of what is, or is not, sex.
</P>
