<HEADER>
A6828 &Cx1f; tdt-z
u a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-CORRECTIVE-HAMPTON-AR     09-21 0081
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CORRECTIVE-HAMPTON-ARRESTED-BOS </SLUG>
  
 (Eds.: Newspapers that used the Boston Globe story HAMPTON-ARRESTED
(a) by John Ellement, which moved Friday, 9/18, will wish to use
the following corrective.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Because of a reporting error, a Boston Globe article about the
arrest of David Edgar Hampton Jr. for allegedly making threats and
stealing checks misidentified the Boston man who says he was
victimized by Hampton. His name is Joseph Keane-Comella.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &UR; The Boston Globe &LR;  &QC;
</P>
</TEXT>
