Clinton-Lewinsky investigation reveal a Linda Tripp even more
Machiavellian and backstabbing than previous known. She gave
seemingly kindly maternal advice to Monica, who told her in
desperate e-mails that she `loved` her and was glad to have her to
confide in. Tripp was so intent on entrapping the lovebirds with
her web of tapes that she may even have doctored a few, according
to legal documents from Kenneth Starr produced along with the
