</P>
<P>
   (NYT18) SEOUL, South Korea -- Sept. 21, 1998 --
OBIT-GRIFFITH-JOYNER, 9-21 -- Florence Griffith Joyner falls to her
knees after winning and setting a world record of 21.34 seconds in
the 200m Gold medal at the 1988 Seoul Olympics. The record still
stands. Griffith Joyner, the three-time gold medalist in Seoul who
revolutionized women's sprinting with her searing speed and
flamboyant fashion sense, died early Monday morning at her home in
Mission Viejo, Calif. She was 38. (Todd Buchanan/1988 New York
Times Photo) *LITE
