<HEADLINE>
ACCOUNTS AND PEOPLE IN THE ADVERTISING WORLD 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN: Texas, Mo., Mich., Ohio)  (nk) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Pearle Selects Barkley Evergreen
</P>
<P>
   Pearle Vision Inc. in Dallas, the unit of the Cole National
Corp. that operates the Pearle Vision Centers retail chain, said
Monday that it had named Barkley Evergreen &AMP; Partners in Kansas
City, Mo., to handle its advertising and marketing account, with
billings estimated at $40 million. The account had been handled by
McCann-Erickson New York, part of the McCann-Erickson Worldwide
Advertising division of McCann-Erickson World Group, a unit of the
Interpublic Group of Companies, until that agency and the company
agreed to part ways last week.
</P>
<P>
   The decision came after a review in which the other participants
were not disclosed. However, Adweek listed three other agencies as
participants: Campbell-Ewald in Warren, Mich., also part of
Interpublic; W.B. DonerW. &AMP; Co. in Southfield, Mich., and Wyse
Advertising in Cleveland.
</P>
<P>
   Candie's Is Seeking Additional Agency
</P>
<P>
   Candie's Inc. said Monday that it was searching for an
additional agency to join its roster as the trendy footwear
marketer expands into the jeans and fragrance categories.
</P>
<P>
   ``Our company is growing and there is just a need to examine the
resources that are out there to help us meet our advertising
goals,'' David Conn, marketing director at Candie's in Purchase,
N.Y., said in confirming reports of the search this week in
Advertising Age and Adweek. Candie's recently signed a licensing
agreement with Liz Claiborne Inc. to market a fragrance, in
addition to agreeing to acquire the Bongo Jeans label to enter the
jeans market.
</P>
<P>
   Conn said that the company was talking to ``a small group of
agencies,'' but he declined to identify them. The additional new
agency would work with Candie's lead shop, In Marketing in Glen
Cove, N.Y., and its in-house group. A decision is expected by the
end of October, he added.
</P>
<P>
   Candie's spent an estimated $8 million on advertising in the
last year. However, the company plans to increase spending to $10
million to $12 million annually, with an additional $7 million to
$9 million on the fragrance with Liz Claiborne. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   People
</P>
<P>
   _ Tom Cotton was named to the new positions of president for
global business and executive vice president and global business
director for the Merrill Lynch &AMP; Co. account at J. Walter Thompson
New York, a unit of WPP Group PLC. He had been executive vice
president and worldwide account director for the AT&AMP;T Corp. account
at Foote, Cone &AMP; Belding, New York, part of True North
Communications.
</P>
<P>
   _ Gerry Lantz was named to the new position of worldwide account
director on the Hasbro Inc. account at Griffin Bacal, New York,
part of the Omnicom Group. He had been corporate marketing director
at Ferrero USA, Somerset, N.J., a unit of the Ferrero Group. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
